<body>
<div class="document-container">

  <!-- DOCUMENT HEADER -->
  <div class="doc-header">
    <div class="doc-title">Private Residential Tenancy Agreement</div>
    <div class="doc-jurisdiction">SCOTLAND</div>
    <div class="premium-badge">PREMIUM</div>
    <div class="doc-subtitle">Professional Tenancy Agreement{{#if guarantor_name}} with Guarantor{{/if}}</div>
    <div class="legal-ref">Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016</div>
    <div class="doc-date">
      <strong>Agreement Date:</strong> {{formatUKDate agreement_date}}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-notice">
    <div class="legal-notice-title">About This Tenancy</div>
    <p>This is a <strong>Private Residential Tenancy (PRT)</strong> under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016. A PRT has <strong>no fixed end date</strong> and continues until properly ended by either party. The Tenant has security of tenure and can only be evicted on grounds specified in the Act, following the correct legal procedures and obtaining an order from the First-tier Tribunal for Scotland.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 1: PARTIES -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">1. Parties</div>

    <div class="subsection-title">The Landlord</div>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Name</td>
        <td class="value">{{landlord_full_name}}{{#if landlord_2_name}} and {{landlord_2_name}}{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Address</td>
        <td class="value">{{landlord_address}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Email</td>
        <td class="value">{{landlord_email}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Telephone</td>
        <td class="value">{{landlord_phone}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{#if landlord_reg_number}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Landlord Registration No.</td>
        <td class="value">{{landlord_reg_number}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{#if registration_authority}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Registered With</td>
        <td class="value">{{registration_authority}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if registration_expiry}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Registration Valid Until</td>
        <td class="value">{{formatUKDate registration_expiry}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{/if}}
    </table>

    {{#unless landlord_reg_number}}
    <div class="warning-notice">
      <div class="warning-notice-title">Landlord Registration Required</div>
      <p>Under the Antisocial Behaviour etc. (Scotland) Act 2004, the Landlord must be registered with the local council. It is a criminal offence to act as an unregistered landlord in Scotland, punishable by a fine of up to £50,000. The Landlord Registration Number must be provided.</p>
    </div>
    {{/unless}}

    {{#if agent_name}}
    <div class="subsection-title">Landlord's Letting Agent</div>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Agent Name</td>
        <td class="value">{{agent_name}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Address</td>
        <td class="value">{{agent_address}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Email</td>
        <td class="value">{{agent_email}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Telephone</td>
        <td class="value">{{agent_phone}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{#if agent_reg_number}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Registration Number</td>
        <td class="value">{{agent_reg_number}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
    </table>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="subsection-title">The Tenant{{#if multiple_tenants}}s{{/if}}</div>
    <table class="tenant-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="width:5%">#</th>
          <th style="width:30%">Full Name</th>
          <th style="width:20%">Date of Birth</th>
          <th style="width:25%">Email</th>
          <th style="width:20%">Telephone</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {{#each tenants}}
        <tr>
          <td>{{this.number}}</td>
          <td>{{this.full_name}}</td>
          <td>{{formatUKDate this.dob}}</td>
          <td>{{this.email}}</td>
          <td>{{this.phone}}</td>
        </tr>
        {{/each}}
      </tbody>
    </table>

    {{#if multiple_tenants}}
    <div class="legal-notice">
      <div class="legal-notice-title">Joint and Several Liability</div>
      <p>Where there is more than one Tenant, each Tenant is jointly and severally liable for all obligations under this Agreement, including the full rent. Any notice served on one Tenant is treated as served on all Tenants. If one Tenant gives notice to end the tenancy, it will normally end the tenancy for all Tenants unless the statutory procedure for joint tenants is followed.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <div class="subsection-title">The Guarantor</div>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Name</td>
        <td class="value">{{guarantor_name}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Address</td>
        <td class="value">{{guarantor_address}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Email</td>
        <td class="value">{{guarantor_email}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Telephone</td>
        <td class="value">{{guarantor_phone}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{#if guarantor_dob}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Date of Birth</td>
        <td class="value">{{formatUKDate guarantor_dob}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if guarantor_relationship}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Relationship to Tenant</td>
        <td class="value">{{guarantor_relationship}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
    </table>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 2: DEFINITIONS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">2. Definitions</div>
    <div class="definition-list">
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Act"</span> means the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016, as amended.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Property"</span> means the dwelling-house described in Schedule 1, including all fixtures, fittings and contents listed in the Inventory.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Landlord"</span> means the person(s) named as landlord in this Agreement and includes successors in title.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Tenant"</span> means the person(s) named as tenant in this Agreement. Where there is more than one tenant, references to "the Tenant" include all tenants jointly and each tenant individually.
      </div>
      {{#if guarantor_name}}
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Guarantor"</span> means the person named as guarantor in this Agreement who has agreed to guarantee the Tenant's obligations.
      </div>
      {{/if}}
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"PRT"</span> means a Private Residential Tenancy under the Act.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Tribunal"</span> means the First-tier Tribunal for Scotland (Housing and Property Chamber).
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Rent"</span> means the rent specified in Schedule 2, payable in accordance with this Agreement.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Deposit"</span> means the security deposit specified in Schedule 2, held in accordance with the Tenancy Deposit Schemes (Scotland) Regulations 2011.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"the Repairing Standard"</span> means the standard prescribed by the Housing (Scotland) Act 2006, as amended.
      </div>
      <div class="definition-item">
        <span class="definition-term">"Working Days"</span> means days other than Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays in Scotland.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 3: THE TENANCY -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">3. The Tenancy</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">3.1</span>
      The Landlord lets the Property to the Tenant as a Private Residential Tenancy under the Act. The Tenant is entitled to occupy the Property as the Tenant's only or principal home.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">3.2</span>
      The tenancy commences on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</strong> and continues indefinitely until ended in accordance with the Act. There is no fixed end date for a PRT.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">3.3</span>
      This tenancy cannot be converted to any other type of tenancy and remains a PRT throughout its duration.
    </div>

    {{#if uses_model_tenancy_terms}}
    <div class="info-box">
      <div class="info-box-title">Scottish Government Model Terms</div>
      <p>This Agreement is based on the Scottish Government's model PRT terms, which provide a standardised framework designed to reduce disputes and ensure compliance with the Act.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 4: RENT -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">4. Rent</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">4.1</span>
      The Tenant shall pay the Rent of <strong>£{{rent_amount}}</strong> per <strong>{{rent_period}}</strong>, payable in advance on the <strong>{{rent_due_day}}</strong> of each {{rent_period}}.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">4.2</span>
      The first payment of <strong>£{{first_payment}}</strong> is due on <strong>{{formatUKDate first_payment_date}}</strong>.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">4.3</span>
      Payment shall be made by <strong>{{payment_method}}</strong> to: {{payment_details}}.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">4.4</span>
      The Rent is payable without deduction or set-off unless the Tenant is legally entitled to make such deduction.
    </div>

    {{#if rent_includes}}
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">4.5</span>
      The Rent includes: {{rent_includes}}.
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    {{#if rent_excludes}}
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if rent_includes}}4.6{{else}}4.5{{/if}}</span>
      The Rent excludes: {{rent_excludes}}. The Tenant is responsible for these costs.
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="subsection-title">Late Payment Interest (Premium)</div>
    <div class="clause">
      If Rent remains unpaid for more than 14 days after the due date, the Landlord may charge interest on the outstanding amount at a rate of 3% above the Bank of England base rate, calculated daily from the due date until payment is received in full.
    </div>

    <div class="subsection-title">Rent Increases</div>
    <div class="clause">
      The Landlord may increase the Rent by serving a Rent Increase Notice (Form 4) on the Tenant, subject to the following:
      <ul class="obligations-list">
        <li>At least <strong>3 months' written notice</strong> must be given;</li>
        <li>The rent cannot be increased more than once in any 12-month period;</li>
        <li>The proposed rent must not exceed the open market rent for a comparable property;</li>
        <li>The Tenant may refer the increase to a Rent Officer if they consider it unreasonable.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    {{#if in_rent_pressure_zone}}
    <div class="legal-notice">
      <div class="legal-notice-title">Rent Pressure Zone</div>
      <p>The Property is located in a designated Rent Pressure Zone (RPZ). Rent increases are subject to additional restrictions and caps as set by the local authority. The Landlord must comply with all RPZ regulations when proposing any rent increase.</p>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 5: DEPOSIT -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">5. Deposit</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">5.1</span>
      The Tenant shall pay a deposit of <strong>£{{deposit_amount}}</strong> on or before the commencement of this tenancy.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">5.2</span>
      Within <strong>30 Working Days</strong> of receiving the Deposit, the Landlord shall:
      <ul class="obligations-list">
        <li>protect the Deposit in an approved tenancy deposit scheme; and</li>
        <li>provide the Tenant with the prescribed information about the protection.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    {{#if deposit_scheme_name}}
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">5.3</span>
      The Deposit will be protected with: <strong>{{deposit_scheme_name}}</strong>.
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if deposit_scheme_name}}5.4{{else}}5.3{{/if}}</span>
      The approved tenancy deposit schemes in Scotland are:
      <ul class="obligations-list">
        <li>SafeDeposits Scotland</li>
        <li>MyDeposits Scotland</li>
        <li>Letting Protection Service Scotland</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if deposit_scheme_name}}5.5{{else}}5.4{{/if}}</span>
      The Deposit is held as security for:
      <ul class="obligations-list">
        <li>damage to the Property, fixtures, fittings or contents (beyond fair wear and tear);</li>
        <li>unpaid Rent;</li>
        <li>unpaid utility bills for which the Tenant is responsible;</li>
        <li>cleaning costs if the Property is not left in an acceptable condition; and</li>
        <li>other breaches of this Agreement.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="warning-notice">
      <div class="warning-notice-title">Failure to Protect Deposit</div>
      <p>If the Landlord fails to protect the Deposit or provide the prescribed information within 30 Working Days, the Tenant may apply to the Tribunal for an order requiring the Landlord to pay the Tenant up to <strong>three times the deposit amount</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {{#if guarantor_name}}
  <!-- SECTION 6: GUARANTOR -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">6. Guarantor</div>

    <div class="guarantor-notice">
      <div class="guarantor-notice-title">Guarantee Agreement</div>
      <p>The Guarantor named in Section 1 hereby guarantees to the Landlord the performance by the Tenant of all obligations under this Agreement and agrees to the following terms:</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.1</span>
      <strong>Joint and Several Liability:</strong> The Guarantor agrees to be jointly and severally liable with the Tenant for all obligations under this Agreement. This means the Guarantor is fully responsible for the Tenant's obligations, not just guaranteeing them.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.2</span>
      <strong>Rent Payment Guarantee:</strong> If the Tenant fails to pay Rent when due, the Guarantor shall pay the outstanding Rent within 14 days of receiving written demand from the Landlord. This includes rent arrears, interest on late payments (as specified in clause 4), and any reasonable costs incurred in recovering the debt.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.3</span>
      <strong>Damage and Dilapidation:</strong> The Guarantor is liable for any damage to the Property beyond fair wear and tear, including cleaning costs, repair costs, and replacement of fixtures, fittings or furnishings damaged by the Tenant.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.4</span>
      <strong>Breach of Agreement:</strong> If the Tenant breaches any term of this Agreement, the Guarantor shall remedy the breach or compensate the Landlord for any losses suffered, including reasonable legal costs.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.5</span>
      <strong>Continuing Guarantee:</strong> This guarantee continues throughout the tenancy and any statutory continuation thereof. The guarantee remains valid even if the tenancy terms are varied by agreement between Landlord and Tenant.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.6</span>
      <strong>Maximum Liability:</strong> The Guarantor's total liability under this guarantee is capped at <strong>twelve months' Rent</strong> (£{{multiply rent_amount 12}}) plus reasonable enforcement costs.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">6.7</span>
      <strong>Independent Legal Advice:</strong> The Guarantor confirms they have been advised to seek independent legal advice before signing this guarantee and understands the full extent of their obligations.
    </div>

    <div class="warning-notice">
      <div class="warning-notice-title">Important Notice to Guarantor</div>
      <p>By signing this Agreement as Guarantor, you are making a serious financial commitment. You will be responsible for paying the Tenant's rent and other obligations if they fail to do so. This could amount to thousands of pounds. <strong>You should seek independent legal advice before signing.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- SECTION 7: TENANT'S OBLIGATIONS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}. Tenant's Obligations</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.1</span>
      <strong>Rent:</strong> Pay the Rent in full and on time without deduction (unless legally entitled).
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.2</span>
      <strong>Utilities:</strong> Pay all charges for gas, electricity, water, sewerage, telephone, internet, council tax (unless included in Rent or exempt), and TV licence during the tenancy.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.3</span>
      <strong>Use of Property:</strong> Use the Property as the Tenant's only or principal home. The Tenant shall not:
      <ul class="obligations-list">
        <li>operate any business from the Property without the Landlord's prior written consent;</li>
        <li>use the Property for any illegal or immoral purpose;</li>
        <li>use the Property for short-term letting (e.g., Airbnb, holiday lets) under any circumstances.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.4</span>
      <strong>Care of Property:</strong> The Tenant shall:
      <ul class="obligations-list">
        <li>take reasonable care of the Property;</li>
        <li>keep the Property in a reasonable state of cleanliness;</li>
        <li>keep the Property adequately heated and ventilated to prevent condensation, dampness and mould;</li>
        <li>report any defects or damage to the Landlord without unreasonable delay;</li>
        <li>not cause damage (fair wear and tear excepted);</li>
        <li>make good any damage caused by the Tenant, household members, or visitors.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.5</span>
      <strong>Alterations:</strong> Not make any alterations, additions or improvements to the Property without the Landlord's prior written consent. If consent is given, the Tenant may be entitled to compensation for improvements at the end of the tenancy.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.6</span>
      <strong>Decorations:</strong> Not remove or alter the Landlord's decorations, fixtures, fittings or furnishings without consent.
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}7{{else}}6{{/if}}.7</span>
